text: Zarevo () is a rural locality (a settlement) and the administrative center of Zarevskoye Rural Settlement of Shovgenovsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 979 as of 2018. There are 11 streets. == Ethnicity == The settlement is inhabited by Russians, Adygheans, Tatars and Armenians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Shovgenovsky District
title: Zarevo, Russia
